        <abstract> 
<p>Glad to hear of MTM’s papers [? "On a peloria and semidouble flower of <hi rend="italic">Ophrys aranifera</hi>, Huds.", <hi rend="italic">J. Linn. Soc. Lond. (Bot.)</hi> 8 (1865): 207–11 and "Observations on the morphology and anatomy of the genus <hi rend="italic">Restio</hi>, Linn.", <hi rend="italic">J. Linn. Soc. Lond. (Bot.)</hi> 8 (1865): 211–55].</p> 
            <p>CD doubts the value, for origin of species, of parallels between peloria in "distinct groups".</p>
            <p>Gärtner proved the stigma can select its own pollen from a mixture of foreign pollens. But much evidence shows varieties of same species are prepotent over a plant’s own pollen.</p>
            <p>MTM’s father [William] believes that variation goes on for a long time once it has commenced.</p>
        </abstract>
